  <li id="comment-23730" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/09314611588187440612" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Maureen</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=586#comment-23730"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-06-26T18:20:31-04:00">Sunday, June 26, 2011 at 6:20 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Steam the eggs, fresh from the farm or not, for 10 minutes and as soon as they are cool enough to handle, they peel perfectly.</p>
<p>I fill the pan that had had the boiling water with cold cold water and let them sit while I peel them one at a time.</p>
<p>Works every time.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=586#comment-23730' data-commentid="23730" data-postid="586" data-belowelement="comment-23730" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Maureen" aria-label='Reply to Maureen'>Reply</a>    </div>
