      <a href="index.html?p=586#comment-23781"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-01-02T01:04:20-05:00">Monday, January 2, 2012 at 1:04 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Amazing recipe. I have never made Deviled Eggs any other way than the &#8220;usual&#8221;, these were wonderful! I probably used less of the yolk filling, because of the addition of the basil aioli.. I am a bit weird about texture, it worked very well. Didn&#39;t fry the capers (got lazy) but drained and dried them off enough to not add any more moisture. Used more basil than I should have.. Didn&#39;t measure correctly.. But it didn&#39;t hurt. Hah!! This recipe is so wonderful because it doesn&#39;t HAVE to be exact. It&#39;s not the portions that make the egg, it&#39;s the initial idea to mix these flavors together! Thank you so much for posting!!! </p>
<p>Had some issues with the hard boiled eggs..figured out that adding salt to the water, and using eggs a week or two old, yields the best peeling experience, had to make them twice, oopsy! ðŸ˜›</p>
<p>Check out the photo, if the link doesn&#39;t work, just copy and paste to your search bar &#8230; <a href="http://www.instagr.am/p/drhKl" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.instagr.am/p/drhKl</a> </p>
<p>-Deanna J Baker</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
